lines.text: I lied to you, betrayed your confidence, and now I've fallen in love with you... too late.
That old man might just reover. Did you ever think of that?
He has regained consciousness. They don't expect him to last the night.
Oh... No, I prefer capital punishment. It's so nice and permanent.
When I operate a place, everything's the best. You'll find that out.
Not if I can help it.
You're not going to turn me in, Dave?

[after a pause]
No... you're going to turn yourself in.
Well, aren't you going to thank me?
Aren't you taking a lot for granted?
I didn't ask for any favors.
I never do any favors, sweetheart. People do favors for me.
Miss Warren, what would you say the odds are of a car being stolen twice in one hour?
